## 3. AsBuilt Import — Payload Contract

### Endpoint

```
POST /api/v1/asbuilt/import
Content-Type: application/json
X-AsBuilt-Key: asbuilt-iq-secret-key-2026
```

### Root-level fields

| Field | Type | Required | Source |
|-------|------|----------|--------|
| `node_id` | string | ✅ | From the user's selection or manual entry. Stored as `skycable_nodes.node_id` |
| `node_name` | string | ✅ | Human-readable name for the node |
| `area_id` | integer | ✅ | Database ID from `GET /asbuilt/sites` response |
| `region` | string | ❌ | e.g. `"CALABARZON"` |
| `province` | string | ❌ | e.g. `"LAGUNA"` |
| `city` | string | ❌ | e.g. `"STA. ROSA"` |
| `poles` | array | ✅ | Array of pole objects (min 1) |
| `spans` | array | ❌ | Array of span objects. Omit or send `[]` if no spans |

### Pole fields (`poles[]`)

| Field | Type | Required | Notes |
|-------|------|----------|-------|
| `pole_index` | integer | ✅ **Required** | **1-based sequential index** within this node. First pole = `1`, second = `2`, etc. This is the ONLY key used by spans to lock to the correct physical pole. Missing = **422 error**. |
| `pole_code` | string | ✅ **Required** | Uppercase pole label from the DXF drawing. e.g. `"NPT"`, `"PL-001"`, `"CV8"` |
| `latitude` | decimal | ✅ **Required** | GPS latitude (−90 to 90). Canvas reader maps X-Y to GPS before sending. |
| `longitude` | decimal | ✅ **Required** | GPS longitude (−180 to 180). Canvas reader maps X-Y to GPS before sending. |

> **`pole_index` is the single most important field.** Two poles can share the same `pole_code` (e.g. multiple "NPT" poles) — `pole_index` is the only way the backend tells them apart.
>
> **Do NOT send `barangay_name` on poles.** It has been removed from the import contract.
>
> **Do NOT send `sequence` on poles.** It is reserved exclusively for the lineman mobile app (PoleMaster teardown order). The backend ignores and never writes it from import payloads.

### Span fields (`spans[]`)

| Field | Type | Required | Notes |
|-------|------|----------|-------|
| `from_pole_code` | string | ✅ | `pole_code` of the starting pole |
| `to_pole_code` | string | ✅ | `pole_code` of the ending pole |
| `from_pole_index` | integer | ✅ **Required** | `pole_index` of the starting pole. Must match a `pole_index` in the `poles` array. Missing or no match = span skipped, recorded in `errors[]`. |
| `to_pole_index` | integer | ✅ **Required** | `pole_index` of the ending pole. Same rules as above. |
| `strand_length` | decimal | ✅ **Required** | Cable length in meters from the OCR reading. `expected_cable = strand_length × number_of_runs` |
| `number_of_runs` | integer | ✅ **Required** | Number of parallel cable runs. Min 1. |
| `components` | object | ❌ | Equipment counts. All fields default to `0` if absent |

> **Spans do NOT carry GPS coordinates.** The canvas reader works with X-Y coordinates only. The backend resolves spans by `pole_index` exclusively — no GPS fallback.

### Components object

```json
{
  "node": 2,
  "amplifier": 1,
  "extender": 0,
  "tsc": 0,
  "powersupply": 0,
  "ps_housing": 0
}
```

