## 9. Testing Checklist

When making changes to the import endpoint, verify:

### Pole-level

- [ ] `pole_index` is saved to `skycable_poles.pole_index` column
- [ ] `sequence` is **never written** from import payload — stays null for new poles
- [ ] `latitude` / `longitude` missing on any pole → `422` validation error
- [ ] `pole_index` missing on any pole → `422` validation error
- [ ] `pole_code` is stored UPPERCASE

### Span-level

- [ ] `from_pole_index` / `to_pole_index` missing on a span → `422` if spans are present
- [ ] `strand_length` / `number_of_runs` missing → `422` if spans are present
- [ ] When 3 poles share `pole_code: "NPT"` with `pole_index` 1, 2, 3 — a span with `from_pole_index: 2` connects to the correct second NPT pole
- [ ] Span with `from_pole_index` that does not match any pole → skipped, recorded in `errors[]`, rest of import succeeds
- [ ] No GPS coordinate matching on spans — `pole_index` only

### Edge cases

- [ ] Re-importing the same payload twice updates existing records (idempotent)
- [ ] Importing to a new node + area creates everything from scratch
- [ ] Span `components` default to `0` when not provided

